MAKURDI – Former Lagos State Commissioner of Police, and renowned critic, Alhaji Abubakar Tsav, is dead. According to his personal assistant, Torkuma Uke, Alhaji Tsav died at Federal Medical Centre, Makurdi, on Monday afternoon. Uke said that his family may likely issue release of his departure later on Monday. Tsav served as Federal Commissioner of Public Complaint Commission in Benue State for a term and was also the Lagos State Commissioner of Police. Benue Govt Drags Tsav To Court Over Inciting Letter June 19, 2017 In "News" MAKURDI - Former Lagos State Commissioner of Police (CP), Abubakar Tsav, said that the removal of Alhaji Umar Fintiri as Acting Governor of Adamawa by the court had rekindled the hope of Nigerians in the judiciary. Tsav, who is an anti-corruption crusader, told the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) on… October 9, 2014 In "News" Makurdi   -      Mr Abubakar Tsav, a former Lagos State Commissioner of Police, has praised President Muhammadu Buhari for working tirelessly to secure the release of the abducted Dapchi schoolgirls. Tsav, currently the Public Complaints Commissioner, overseeing Benue, told the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) on Thursday in… March 22, 2018 In "News"